-- Jamaican GDP Fell 0.6% in Fourth Quarter Due to Hurricane
-- B y   E r i c   S a b o
-- 2013-02-21T23:04:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-21/jamaican-gdp-fell-0-6-in-fourth-quarter-due-to-hurricane.html
Jamaica’s economy shrank 0.6 percent
in the fourth quarter from the same period last year, the
 Finance Ministry ’s planning agency said.  Damage from Hurricane Sandy and “slower than anticipated
recovery” in the global economy caused the contraction, marking
a full-year the Caribbean island has experienced no growth, the
agency said today on its  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Sabo in Panama City at 
 esabo1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Faries at 
 wfaries@bloomberg.net . 